We first extract the needed figures from the provided statements.

Step 1. Calculate Return on Equity (ROE)
• Net Profit (from Income Statement): 835266.51 
• Owner’s Equity – use the average over the period:
  Initial Owner's Equity = 13000000.00  
  Ending Owner's Equity = 13835266.51  
  Average Owner’s Equity = (13000000.00 + 13835266.51) / 2 = 13417633.255  
• ROE = Net Profit / Average Owner’s Equity = 835266.51 / 13417633.255 ≈ 0.06226 or 6.23%

Step 2. Debt to Asset Ratio
• Total Liabilities – here it is the “Total Current Liabilities” = 378850.51  
• Total Assets (from Balance Sheet) = 14214117.02  
• Debt to Asset Ratio = 378850.51 / 14214117.02 ≈ 0.02664, which rounds to 0.03

Step 3. Gross Profit Margin
• Gross Profit (from Income Statement) = 1622011.03  
• Total Revenue = 2637011.03  
• Gross Profit Margin = Gross Profit / Total Revenue = 1622011.03 / 2637011.03 ≈ 0.6155 or 61.55%

Thus, the final answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Return on Equity (ROE)": "6.23%",
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.03",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "61.55%"
  }
}
